RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAY SASSY stalked the pace racing in hand, moved up three-wide nearing the quarter pole, caught the leaders nearing the eighth pole, dueled with HANNAHAZA HETTY from that point and prevailed narrowly in a stiff drive. HANNAHAZA HETTY saved ground while being forwardly placed, was in tight lacking room nearing the three-eighths pole, angled out two-wide splitting rivals nearing the quarter pole, dueled for the lead the final eighth and just missed in a tough decision. NORTHERN LINCHPIN was allowed to settle early while three-wide, moved up four-wide nearing the quarter pole and finished in a mild rally. SENSIBLE LUTE saved ground setting the pace to the eighth pole and then weakened late. HOLDMYGOLDMISSY hopped slightly at the start, then was two-wide while being unhurried and failed to menace. CLEARWATER BELLE dropped back while saving ground and was not a threat. LIBBY'S GAMBIT was four-wide while racing in the middle of the field and gave way before going a half mile.

OUT OF STARS was reserved off the early pace, moved up five-wide nearing the quarter pole and finished fast. DRINKUP BUTTERCUP vied for the lead into the stretch from along the inside and weakened slightly late. BIKINI NATION saved ground while being allowed to settle but lacked a rally when asked. PRINCESS PAYTON was unhurried after breaking a step slow, came three-wide into the stretch and failed to seriously threaten. SETTLER'S COVE disputed the early pace while three-wide and tired. G G RULES dropped back after bobbling at the start and was not a factor.

Washington Bred Claiming Price $12,500.

COBRA JET prompted A VIEW FROM ABOVE from along the inside, took the lead nearing the eighth pole but was unable to resist the winner late in a fame try. A VIEW FROM ABOVE set the pressured pace into the stretch from along the outside and held on fairly well for third. MAHI MAHI settled in the middle of the pack early, moved up six-wide nearing the quarter pole but lacked a rally. LEPRINO stumbled at the start to get away behind the field then was unhurried, came two-wide into the stretch but was unable to recover the lost ground. MARCH ON LINCH was forwardly placed early while racing three-wide, came five-wide into the stretch and tired. SPROSTON settled in the middle of the field early but gave way after a half mile. RIP CITY steadied briefly from between horses on the far turn, then dropped far back and was distanced.
